Active Directory Lab 🖥️
📌 Overview

This project is a hands-on Active Directory Lab built using Windows Server. It is designed to simulate a real enterprise environment where you can practice and learn core IT support and system administration skills.

The lab focuses on Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS) configuration, user management, group policies, and basic network troubleshooting.

🎯 Objectives
Set up a Windows Server as a Domain Controller
Install and configure Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)
Create and manage users, groups, and organizational units (OUs)
Join client machines to the domain
Apply Group Policies (GPO)
Practice basic IT troubleshooting scenarios
🛠️ Technologies Used
Windows Server (2016/2019/2022)
Windows
